 {"id":"bd-2crr","title":"Create unified Embedder + Reranker traits and model registry","description":"## Task: Create Unified Model Traits and Registry

Define the trait interfaces that all embedding and reranker backends implement,
plus a registry that produces the correct backend from configuration.

## Embedder Trait Design
```rust
/// Category of embedding model (for benchmark classification)
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub enum ModelCategory {
    StaticEmbedder,       // Model2Vec, static-retrieval-mrl
    TransformerEmbedder,  // MiniLM, BGE, Nomic, Gemma (ONNX inference)
}

/// Sync trait: all methods block. Daemon backend wraps async UDS in block_on().
pub trait Embedder: Send + Sync {
    /// Embed a batch of texts, returning normalized vectors
    fn embed_batch(&self, texts: &[&str]) -> Result<Vec<Vec<f32>>>;
    /// Native embedding dimensions
    fn dimensions(&self) -> usize;
    /// Human-readable model identifier
    fn model_name(&self) -> &str;
    /// Model category for benchmark classification
    fn category(&self) -> ModelCategory;
    /// Whether this model supports Matryoshka truncation
    fn supports_mrl(&self) -> bool { false }
    /// Truncate embeddings to target_dim (only if supports_mrl)
    /// IMPORTANT: Must re-normalize after truncation!
    fn truncate(&self, embeddings: &[Vec<f32>], target_dim: usize) -> Result<Vec<Vec<f32>>> {
        if target_dim > self.dimensions() {
            anyhow::bail!("target_dim {} > native dims {}", target_dim, self.dimensions());
        }
        Ok(embeddings.iter().map(|e| {
            let truncated: Vec<f32> = e[..target_dim].to_vec();
            let norm = truncated.iter().map(|x| x * x).sum::<f32>().sqrt();
            truncated.iter().map(|x| x / norm).collect()
        }).collect())
    }
}
```

